12
00:00:50,008 --> 00:00:52,790
A magnetic spectrometer is used
to measure the direction and

13
00:00:52,790 --> 00:00:55,840
momentum of a particle
with minimal interaction.

14
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:58,300
It is a nondestructive method
to measure these properties.

15
00:00:59,410 --> 00:01:03,130
The particle trajectory is measured
in a known magnetic field.

16
00:01:03,130 --> 00:01:07,990
For a homogeneous field, the trajectory is
a spiral, a circle in the plane orthogonal

17
00:01:07,990 --> 00:01:11,810
to the field, and a straight line
in the direction of the field.

18
00:01:11,810 --> 00:01:16,968
The radius of curvature is proportional to
what is called the magnetic rigidity R,

19
00:01:16,968 --> 00:01:20,743
which is the ratio between the momentum p,
and the charge Z.

20
00:01:20,743 --> 00:01:25,424
R = p/Z, and can be
measured by the product of the radius

21
00:01:25,424 --> 00:01:29,030
of curvature and the magnetic field.

22
00:01:29,030 --> 00:01:33,682
The magnetic field itself is provided by
a permanent magnet or an electromagnet.

23
00:01:33,682 --> 00:01:37,405
Measurements of the path are performed
by an ionization detector,

24
00:01:37,405 --> 00:01:41,860
a gas filled wire chamber, for example,
or layers of semiconductor detectors.

25
00:01:42,910 --> 00:01:46,490
The tangent to the trajectory
at the entry of the magnet

26
00:01:46,490 --> 00:01:48,829
gives the direction of
the incident particle.

27
